The CD@CNF membrane showed recycle-ability toward MB rejection up to third cycle, having 95% of rejection rate (Fig. 9
                     (a)). Moreover, the CD@CNF membrane showed better cationic dye selectivity than the CNF membrane even in the presence of anionic and neutral dyes (Fig. 9(b)). The CD@CNF membrane showed good dye selectivity regardless of loading amounts (Fig. 9(c)). The CD@CNF membrane selectively rejected cationic dye from the mixed solution of MB and OG (Table 1
                     ).
